#extend("base"):
    #export("content"):
        <section class="page-header">
            <div class="container">
                <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
                <p class="page-subtitle">Last updated: February 2026</p>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="section">
            <div class="container">
                <div class="content-prose">
                    <h2>Introduction</h2>
                    <p>
                        AgentKey ("we", "our", or "us") is committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy
                        explains how we collect, use, and share information when you use our service.
                    </p>

                    <h2>Information We Collect</h2>

                    <h3>Information You Provide</h3>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Account Information</strong> - When you authenticate via StrongDM ID, we receive
                            your subject identifier and display name.</li>
                        <li><strong>Profile Information</strong> - You may optionally provide a description, homepage URL,
                            and avatar URL.</li>
                        <li><strong>Public Keys</strong> - You upload public cryptographic keys for signature verification.
                            These are public by design.</li>
                        <li><strong>Identity Proofs</strong> - You may add proofs linking your account to external
                            identities (domains, GitHub accounts).</li>
                    </ul>

                    <h3>Information Collected Automatically</h3>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Activity Logs</strong> - We log actions taken on your account (key additions,
                            profile updates) for security purposes.</li>
                        <li><strong>IP Addresses</strong> - We may log IP addresses for security and rate limiting.</li>
                        <li><strong>Usage Data</strong> - We collect basic analytics about how the service is used.</li>
                    </ul>

                    <h2>How We Use Your Information</h2>
                    <ul>
                        <li>To provide the AgentKey service and verify agent identities</li>
                        <li>To display your public profile to other users</li>
                        <li>To verify signature requests against your registered public keys</li>
                        <li>To maintain security and prevent abuse</li>
                        <li>To improve our service</li>
                    </ul>

                    <h2>Information Sharing</h2>

                    <h3>Public Information</h3>
                    <p>
                        The following information is public by design and accessible to anyone:
                    </p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Your subject identifier</li>
                        <li>Your display name</li>
                        <li>Your profile description (if provided)</li>
                        <li>Your public keys</li>
                        <li>Your verified identity proofs</li>
                        <li>Your sponsor (if sponsored)</li>
                    </ul>

                    <h3>Private Information</h3>
                    <p>
                        We do not sell your private information. We may share information:
                    </p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>With service providers who help us operate AgentKey</li>
                        <li>To comply with legal obligations</li>
                        <li>To protect our rights and prevent abuse</li>
                    </ul>

                    <h2>Data Retention</h2>
                    <p>
                        We retain your information as long as your account is active. You can delete your account
                        at any time, which will remove your profile and keys from public view. Activity logs may
                        be retained for security purposes.
                    </p>

                    <h2>Security</h2>
                    <p>
                        We implement appropriate security measures to protect your information. However, no system
                        is completely secure. You are responsible for keeping your private keys secure.
                    </p>

                    <h2>Your Rights</h2>
                    <p>You have the right to:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Access your personal information</li>
                        <li>Correct inaccurate information</li>
                        <li>Delete your account and associated data</li>
                        <li>Export your data</li>
                    </ul>

                    <h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
                    <p>
                        We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of significant
                        changes by posting a notice on our website.
                    </p>

                    <h2>Contact Us</h2>
                    <p>
                        If you have questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us through the
                        information provided on our website.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>
    #endexport
#endextend
